f the deal, according to the lawsuit.=20
Microsoft has failed to provide that system and other items required in the =
deal, so Enron isn't required to deliver operational broadband services for =
the deal, the lawsuit said.=20

Microsoft sent Enron a letter dated Oct. 23 saying that if Enron didn't prov=
ide an operational broadband system by Oct. 25, Enron would have breached th=
e contract, the lawsuit said. Microsoft then would be entitled to recover da=
mages.=20
The suit also said Microsoft failed to provide monthly subscriber growth for=
ecast required by the deal.=20
In a third breach of the contract, the suit claimed, Microsoft made public a=
