 also asked that Enron be allowed to recover unspecified damages as well as =
costs stemming from the lawsuit.=20
Neither Enron nor Microsoft have responded to requests for comment on the la=
wsuit.=20
The Microsoft deal is the second failed broadband agreement. In July 2000, E=
nron and Blockbuster Video, a unit of Viacom Inc. (VIA), announced a deal to=
 deliver movies over the Internet.=20
That deal fell apart in March of this year when Blockbuster said Enron's fib=
er-optic network couldn't deliver the service on a dependable basis. Enron c=
ountered that Blockbuster couldn't deliver the quality and quantity of movie=
